name: Yoga and Pilates Club
description: A safe space for MBA students to prioritize wellness while bonding over an enjoyment for yoga, pilates and fitness through in-person and virtual classes from certified instructors.

name: Yooper Club
description: The Yooper Club is dedicated to helping those from the Upper Peninsula and other rural areas feel a sense of community and to help those interested learn about the U.P. as well. We host various events to embrace the things we know and love from the U.P.

name: Young Americans for Freedom
description: YAF is a non-profit, non-partisan organization that brings students together to advocate for the ideas of limited government, individual freedom, free enterprise, and a strong national defense.

name: Young Democratic Socialists of America at the University of Michigan
description: We are this university's DSA (Democratic Socialists of America) chapter. Our mission is to educate and organize students and young people in unique positions as students to play a principled role in the movement for social and economic justice.

name: Zeta Omega Eta
description: Zeta Omega Eta is a non-traditional and intersectional sorority that aims to bring strong, passionate people together to redefine what it means to be a feminist and sorority member.

name: Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Inc. Gamma Delta Chapter
description: As one of nine historically Black fraternities and sororities, Zeta Phi Beta Sorority, Inc. is “a community conscious, action-oriented organization,” striving to uphold and exemplify the ideals of scholarship, service, sisterly love, and Finer Womanhood.

name: Zeta Pi, Professional Technology Fraternity
description: Co-ed Professional Technology Fraternity established in 2023 at the University of Michigan.

name: Zeta Tau Alpha
description: A member in good standing of the Panhellenic Association, Zeta Tau Alpha is a recognized University student organization. For more information on this sorority, contact the chapter president.

name: Zouk Dance Club
description: A dance club intended for everyone interested in Brazilian Zouk dance, body rolls, and excessive hair whips. We meet weekly for beginner classes, socials, informal practicas and workshops lead by internationally acclaimed Zouk instructors.

name: [RE]vive Refugee Education Initiative
description: [RE]vive is a refugee education initiative, founded in 2017 at the University of Michigan. [RE]vive's mission is to bring educational and vocational resources to empower refugee students to apply to higher education opportunities, scholarships, and jobs.
